@30038 = ~Inscribed upon the blade of this dagger is the word "Enough!"  Judging by the skill of the craftsman and the enchantments on the blade, it may have its origins within some fierce school of debate in Cormyr or elsewhere, perhaps as a way to signal the end of a debate, or to end an argument by other, bloodier, means.  When hurled, the dagger's accuracy and swift flight enchantments cause it to fly far and true into whatever target the wielder wishes. It doesn't look to have seen much use or combat, so it may have been intended as a purely ornamental weapon.

