@33262 = ~This small leather sling has the embossed image of a cat on its back.  It was crafted for a small, wily thief from Waterdeep named Pesker the Cat.  The spry, energetic man kept the sling tucked into the back of his breeches wherever he went.  To onlookers, it often appeared to be a small tail dancing behind him as he skipped along.  When Pesker heard the image described to him, he decided to have the cat embossed on the sling's leather.  Pesker had to flee enemies in Waterdeep in 1211 DR.  He left most of his belongings behind, including this sling.

