//OHTEMPUS
@70774 = ~priest of Tempus~
@70775 = ~Priest of Tempus~
@70776 = ~PRIEST OF TEMPUS: Tempus, also known as the Lord of Battles or the Foehammer, is random in his favors, yet his chaotic nature favors all sides equally. Lord Tempus may be on an army's side one day and against them the next; such is the nature of war. Tempuran clergy can be found on both sides of a conflict, as none can ever truly know whom the war god will favor.

Advantages:
- May cast Holy Power once per day. Gains one use at level 1 and an additional use every 5 levels thereafter.
- May cast Chaos of Battle once per day. Gains one use at level 1 and an additional use every 10 levels thereafter.

CHAOS OF BATTLE: Chaos of Battle applies bonuses to all allies and penalties to all enemies within a 30-ft. radius of the caster. The spell lasts 1 turn and will randomly affect the targets' Armor Class, Hit Points, THAC0, saves, or luck. The magnitude of the effect starts at 1 (5 for Hit Points) at level 1 and will improve by 1 (5 for Hit Points) every 6 levels of the caster.

Disadvantages:
 Alignment restricted to chaotic good, chaotic neutral, chaotic evil, or true neutral.~
@70777 = ~Less than two weeks after your initiation ceremony at the Tempus Temple, you have been summoned to the Elder Swordsman of your Order. In words that promise the glory of faith, he gave you the first assignment you will undertake as a true member of the Order. You will fearlessly travel North and contact the local temple in Easthaven. In addition, the Elder Swordsman, as if not attaching much importance to this, mentioned that he was "worried" about some omens regarding events in the North. He is sure that if in these troubled times there is still valor and glory, it should be in the service of the Lord of Battle.

It may not be a lot of glory to travel the frozen slopes of the Spine of the World, but you are eager to hit the road. After all, this is an opportunity to show the peoples of the North the courage and valor that came from the cities of the South, as well as to avoid the boredom of daily polishing of the armor of the supreme clergy of the temple. You agree without hesitation; and in ten days you are already on a ship going to the North, armed only with a staff in your hands and loud battle hymns in your heart.~
